            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip #2: Use the \"Subject\" Structure Like a Pro",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Trainual organizes content into a hierarchy: ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Business → Subject → Topic → Step",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ". Understanding this structure early saves you from a disorganized mess later.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's how I recommend setting it up:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Business Level",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This is your company playbook. It covers company-wide policies, mission, values, and org charts.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Subject Level",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Think of subjects as departments or functions: Marketing, Sales, Operations, Finance, HR. Each subject contains the processes relevant to that area.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Topic Level",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "These are individual processes within a subject. Under \"Marketing,\" you might have topics like \"Content Calendar Management,\" \"Social Media Posting,\" and \"Email Newsletter Workflow.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step Level",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Each topic breaks into clear, numbered steps. This is where the real magic happens—new hires can follow steps without needing to ask a colleague.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The beauty of this structure is that it mirrors how people think about work. Nobody searches for \"the thing where we update the spreadsheet on Tuesdays.\" They search for \"Finance → Payroll → Processing Payroll.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l5",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/trainual-use-cases"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Want to dive deeper? Check out this ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "complete use cases guide",
            "marks": [
              "l5"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " for real examples of how different teams structure their content.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip #3: Leverage Quizzes and Tracking for Accountability",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's a feature that separates Trainual from basic documentation tools: ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "built-in quizzes and completion tracking.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "When you assign a training module to a team member, you can:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Track progress",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – see exactly where they are in the material",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Add quizzes",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – verify they actually understood the content (not just clicked \"next\")",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Require sign-offs",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – have employees acknowledge they've read and understood key policies",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "View analytics",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – identify who's falling behind or which content needs improvement",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This matters more than you think. Without accountability, documentation becomes shelfware. People skim it once and forget. With Trainual's tracking, you create a culture where learning the playbook is expected—and measured.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For compliance-heavy industries (healthcare, finance, food service), the sign-off feature alone is worth the investment. You get a clear record that someone completed required training, with timestamps.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip #4: Record Your SOPs with Video",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Reading a wall of text is nobody's idea of a good time. Trainual lets you embed videos directly into your steps, and I strongly recommend using this for:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Software walkthroughs",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – screen recordings of how to use your CRM, project management tool, or internal systems",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Physical processes",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – how to operate equipment, set up a workstation, or handle a specific client interaction",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Context-heavy explanations",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " – where tone, nuance, or visual cues matter more than written words",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You don't need professional production quality. A quick Loom recording with your face in the corner, walking through the process, is 10x more effective than a 500-word written guide. Trainual supports embedded video natively, so your team watches without leaving the platform.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bonus: when the process changes, you just re-record and swap the video. No rewriting paragraphs of instructions.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
